[floorboard creaking]

15:06.305 --> 15:08.107
[bottles clink]

15:18.917 --> 15:20.185
[man groans]

15:20.218 --> 15:21.786
-[gasps]
-[glass shatters]

15:21.820 --> 15:24.957
[man gasping]

15:34.566 --> 15:37.535
[Wesley in English]
You already took...

15:37.569 --> 15:39.705
took everything.

15:48.047 --> 15:50.983
[in English] What-- What--
What happened to you?

15:54.686 --> 15:58.290
They left me to die.

16:02.728 --> 16:05.164
Who?

16:05.197 --> 16:07.766
[groans]

16:07.799 --> 16:10.970
[rasping breaths]

16:26.785 --> 16:28.420
[speaking Romanian]

17:07.860 --> 17:10.763
[somber music]

17:46.965 --> 17:48.534
[Wesley groaning]

18:01.112 --> 18:02.781
-[Wesley groaning]
-[indistinct chatter]

18:07.185 --> 18:10.289
[groaning continues]

18:28.273 --> 18:30.342
Please, please don't.
Please.

18:36.280 --> 18:38.250
Please, please, I can help you.

18:38.283 --> 18:40.452
I can get you out of here,
out of the country.

18:41.686 --> 18:42.821
Ah, I swear!

18:42.855 --> 18:45.023
I can take you with me
to Canada.

18:45.056 --> 18:46.558
That's where I'm from.

18:48.159 --> 18:50.262
[in English] How?

18:50.295 --> 18:52.564
My dad's a businessman, okay?
He's rich.

18:52.597 --> 18:54.866
He made a plan for me to escape
when the borders closed,

18:54.899 --> 18:57.268
but I was robbed, hurt,
and I missed the connection,

18:57.301 --> 18:59.671
but I still have contact
with the smugglers.

18:59.704 --> 19:01.239
<i> Contrabandisti.</i>

19:01.273 --> 19:04.342
Okay, I can tell them
I have friends.

19:04.375 --> 19:06.811
We can all leave together and...

19:06.845 --> 19:10.949
and my dad will reward you
once I'm... I'm home.

19:10.983 --> 19:12.784
You can be rich too.

19:22.527 --> 19:25.697
[in English]
Okay, you give me the name
of the<i> Contrabandisti,</i>

19:25.730 --> 19:29.301
and I will see
if you tell the truth.

19:29.801 --> 19:31.403
-Yes?
-Yes.

19:32.103 --> 19:34.072
Yes.
Thank you.

19:34.106 --> 19:35.707
[speaking Romanian]

19:47.084 --> 19:49.020
[exhales]

19:49.054 --> 19:50.555
What did he say?

19:50.589 --> 19:53.258
[in English] He say
if are trouble, he kill you.

19:54.459 --> 19:55.660
[groans]

19:55.693 --> 19:57.662
Okay.

19:57.695 --> 19:59.765
-[Wesley] Okay.
-[Nikolai] Let's go.

19:59.798 --> 20:01.599
-[both straining]
-[Wesley] Okay, oi, fuck.

20:01.632 --> 20:04.403
I just, uh...
I just need a minute.

20:07.272 --> 20:09.174
I'm sorry.

20:09.207 --> 20:12.277
[groans, breathing heavily]

20:20.051 --> 20:22.487
-[panting]
-[unzips bag]

20:29.294 --> 20:30.862
This yours?

20:30.896 --> 20:33.131
[chuckles]

20:33.164 --> 20:35.266
No, it's, uh...

20:35.299 --> 20:36.935
it's the family's
I was staying with.

20:38.302 --> 20:39.771
The little girl's.

20:42.874 --> 20:46.378
Maybe it means we have
luckier days ahead.

20:46.411 --> 20:48.914
Some people think goldfish
bring good fortune.

20:50.882 --> 20:52.617
A fish?

20:52.651 --> 20:54.920
No.

20:54.953 --> 20:57.455
Yeah.

20:57.489 --> 20:59.857
Hey, maybe it already has.

20:59.891 --> 21:01.693
[zips bag]

21:04.228 --> 21:06.365
I'm Wesley, by the way.

21:07.632 --> 21:08.900
Nikolai.

21:10.669 --> 21:12.737
Thank you.

21:12.771 --> 21:17.075
Nikolai, you--
You saved my life.

21:17.109 --> 21:20.746
[gentle music]

21:32.123 --> 21:34.693
[upbeat music playing]

21:39.865 --> 21:41.867
[speaking Romanian]

21:55.380 --> 21:56.748
[Serghei clears throat]

23:16.127 --> 23:18.397
[in English]<i> Risky Business.</i>

23:20.599 --> 23:22.434
[speaking Romanian]

23:44.188 --> 23:45.724
[grunts]

24:18.189 --> 24:21.092
[gentle piano music]

24:34.739 --> 24:35.941
[sighs]

24:50.055 --> 24:52.958
[tense music]

24:57.161 --> 24:58.830
Milos?

25:05.403 --> 25:07.872
Milos.

25:07.906 --> 25:11.409
[somber music]

25:11.442 --> 25:14.312
Nikolai.

25:14.346 --> 25:16.281
[speaking Romanian]

25:16.314 --> 25:18.049
[playing piano]

25:23.254 --> 25:24.222
[Wesley]<i> Are you okay?</i>

25:28.226 --> 25:29.661
What are you doing?

25:29.694 --> 25:31.796
Piano's out of tune.
Thought I could fix it for you.

25:31.829 --> 25:33.497
No, no, no, no, no.
Don't touch it.

25:33.531 --> 25:35.099
Don't touch it!
Stop!

25:35.133 --> 25:37.068
[single piano note]

25:37.101 --> 25:38.303
Fuck, stop.

25:50.615 --> 25:52.117
Did you travel again?

25:57.288 --> 25:58.723
Bad dream.

26:00.959 --> 26:01.893
Does it hurt?

26:05.129 --> 26:06.064
When you do it?

26:07.932 --> 26:10.068
[sighs]

26:14.405 --> 26:15.574
What are you writing?

26:16.474 --> 26:18.009
Nothing, I--

26:21.712 --> 26:25.917
I haven't heard from my family
since the border closed.

26:27.318 --> 26:30.121
I write letters home
even though I can't send them.

26:32.557 --> 26:34.759
I'm sorry about yours.

26:36.293 --> 26:37.929
About your family.

26:47.172 --> 26:49.540
My--

26:49.573 --> 26:52.944
My uncle say I'm<i> Moroi.</i>

26:54.245 --> 26:55.714
A ghost.

26:57.582 --> 27:00.618
He-- He think--

27:00.651 --> 27:02.520
He think I die in church

27:02.554 --> 27:05.589
and my spirit

27:05.623 --> 27:09.961
is trapped between
heaven and hell.

27:11.195 --> 27:14.265
I tried to find my way
to my family,

27:14.298 --> 27:18.637
but this is as...

27:19.770 --> 27:22.707
as close as I can get.

27:27.445 --> 27:29.280
You don't look dead to me.

27:31.782 --> 27:33.718
What do you think it is?

27:37.955 --> 27:41.960
I-- I think I just want
to see them again.

27:45.730 --> 27:47.298
[clears throat softly]

27:47.332 --> 27:50.035
[somber music]

27:58.643 --> 28:00.812
When people don't
understand something,

28:00.845 --> 28:03.081
they tend to make up stories
to help.

28:09.487 --> 28:10.989
Like that goldfish.

28:13.324 --> 28:16.895
It can only comprehend
what's in its bowl.

28:18.829 --> 28:20.865
That's its whole world.

28:20.899 --> 28:23.868
Maybe you need to get out
of your bowl.

28:25.069 --> 28:27.105
See that this isn't
all there is.

28:37.015 --> 28:40.385
Yes, you-- You put
the nail in my head.

28:41.419 --> 28:43.588
What?

28:43.621 --> 28:44.856
The--

28:44.889 --> 28:46.958
You put the nail in my head.

28:46.991 --> 28:49.860
Oh, no, it's--
[chuckles]

28:49.894 --> 28:52.697
"You hit the nail on the head."

28:52.730 --> 28:54.532
Like, "You hit
the point exactly."

28:54.566 --> 28:57.102
Yes, but you--
You do not hit the point.

28:57.135 --> 28:59.503
You hit the head.

28:59.537 --> 29:01.773
You-- You know what?

29:01.806 --> 29:03.807
You're right,
that works too.

29:03.841 --> 29:06.077
-[both chuckle]
-Yes, of course it work.

29:06.110 --> 29:08.246
-Nail in my head.
-Nail in your head.

29:08.279 --> 29:11.449
[both laugh]

29:23.761 --> 29:26.197
[floorboards creak]

29:26.231 --> 29:29.501
[tense music]

30:03.367 --> 30:05.103
[soft creaking]

30:19.550 --> 30:21.553
[DJ speaking Romanian on radio]

30:27.358 --> 30:29.427
Whoo-hoo-hoo-hoo!

30:29.460 --> 30:31.596
[Black Flag's "Rise Above"]

30:31.629 --> 30:32.864
<i> ♪ Jealous cowards ♪</i>

30:32.897 --> 30:34.064
[both singing along]
<i> ♪ Try to control ♪</i>

30:34.098 --> 30:36.000
<i> ♪ Rise above
We gotta rise above ♪</i>

30:36.034 --> 30:38.369
<i> ♪ They distort what we say ♪</i>

30:38.403 --> 30:41.071
<i> ♪ Rise above
We're gonna rise above ♪</i>

30:41.105 --> 30:43.841
<i> ♪ Try and stop what we do ♪</i>

30:43.875 --> 30:45.777
<i> ♪ Rise above
We're gonna rise above ♪</i>

30:45.810 --> 30:47.545
<i> ♪ When they can't
Do it themselves ♪</i>

30:47.579 --> 30:50.214
<i> ♪ Rise above
We're gonna rise above ♪</i>

30:50.247 --> 30:54.685
<i>♪ We are tired of your abuse ♪</i>

30:54.719 --> 30:57.421
<i> ♪ Try to stop us ♪</i>

30:57.454 --> 30:59.490
<i> ♪ It's no use ♪</i>

30:59.523 --> 31:01.225
[Serghei speaking Romanian]

31:01.258 --> 31:02.860
<i>♪ Society's arms of control ♪</i>

31:02.894 --> 31:05.196
<i> ♪ Rise above
We're gonna rise above ♪</i>

31:05.230 --> 31:07.031
<i> [music stops]</i>

31:13.104 --> 31:14.906
Ah.

31:17.742 --> 31:21.578
[Wesley in English]
I saw the Ramones
in Toronto in '83.

31:21.612 --> 31:23.748
No way, no way.
How was it?

31:23.781 --> 31:27.151
Yeah, wild.
Joey Ramone is a legend.

31:27.184 --> 31:29.086
<i> Ce misto.</i>
That is so cool.

31:29.120 --> 31:32.123
Hey, you ever think
you could travel there?

31:32.156 --> 31:33.324
With what you can do,

31:33.357 --> 31:36.427
like see the Ramones
in Toronto

31:36.460 --> 31:38.529
and the Clash in Tokyo
in the same day.

31:39.564 --> 31:43.534
Uh... no.

31:43.567 --> 31:48.039
I already told you,
it doesn't work like that.

31:48.072 --> 31:51.609
I am-- I am tied to my home.

31:51.642 --> 31:52.977
I only come here.

31:53.010 --> 31:57.047
Yeah, for now, but...

31:57.081 --> 31:58.950
what if you could do more?

32:00.450 --> 32:02.887
See more?

32:02.920 --> 32:04.722
Nikolai, you are not a ghost.

32:04.756 --> 32:07.257
You're alive.

32:07.291 --> 32:09.827
For whatever reason,
you're still here.

32:09.861 --> 32:12.596
And my dad, he has connections,
friends who could help you.

32:12.630 --> 32:16.567
[uneasy music]

32:16.601 --> 32:20.838
Shit, Nikolai, if I didn't have
something your uncle wanted,

32:20.871 --> 32:22.573
I'd be dead.

32:29.246 --> 32:34.085
Hey, all I'm saying is you
have more power than you think.

32:34.118 --> 32:36.754
-[plane engine hums]
-[distant explosion]

32:36.787 --> 32:38.656
[indistinct shouting]

32:38.689 --> 32:40.891
[gunfire]

32:40.925 --> 32:42.826
Is that close?

32:42.860 --> 32:46.030
Uh, no, we are good.

32:55.039 --> 32:56.407
[speaking Romanian]

33:22.666 --> 33:24.569
[in English, then Romanian]
No, no, no. No.

33:28.773 --> 33:30.708
[in English] No, no.

33:39.817 --> 33:41.719
[breathes deeply]

33:44.155 --> 33:46.157
[birds chirping]

33:50.761 --> 33:52.663
[indistinct chatter]

34:02.507 --> 34:05.443
[gentle music]

34:09.046 --> 34:12.850
[both speaking Romanian]

34:12.884 --> 34:14.886
[bells chime]

34:14.919 --> 34:16.653
[Milos]<i> Nikolai.</i>

34:16.687 --> 34:18.656
[gunfire]

34:19.823 --> 34:21.525
[indistinct shouting]

34:21.559 --> 34:23.727
[breathing heavily]

34:23.761 --> 34:26.697
[tense music]

34:37.708 --> 34:38.843
Nikolai...

34:39.810 --> 34:41.445
[gasping]

34:41.478 --> 34:43.181
[explosion]

34:45.248 --> 34:47.151
-[in English] Shit.
-[high-pitched ringing]

34:47.885 --> 34:49.087
[Wesley] Nikolai.

34:51.556 --> 34:53.490
Are you okay?

34:53.524 --> 34:54.725
Hey.

34:57.261 --> 35:01.065
Nikolai, just take slow,
deep breaths.

35:01.098 --> 35:04.334
[breathes deeply]

35:04.368 --> 35:06.103
Your hand,
squeeze it into a fist.

35:06.137 --> 35:07.638
Okay, do what I do.

35:07.671 --> 35:10.074
[both breathing deeply)

35:10.107 --> 35:12.577
-There you go.
-[sniffles]

35:15.580 --> 35:17.915
What happened?

35:17.948 --> 35:21.786
[breathes deeply, sniffles]

35:25.656 --> 35:27.925
They're dead

35:27.959 --> 35:29.894
because of me.

35:32.062 --> 35:33.798
[sniffles]

35:40.004 --> 35:44.842
This trick you learn,

35:44.875 --> 35:48.246
you learn from sister?

35:49.012 --> 35:50.581
From her asthma attack?

35:54.385 --> 35:56.853
You read my letters.

35:56.887 --> 35:58.422
I--

35:59.757 --> 36:01.692
I didn't trust you.

36:06.464 --> 36:07.698
[sniffles]

36:12.636 --> 36:14.271
[sighs]

36:14.304 --> 36:17.375
Your sister, how old?

36:17.775 --> 36:19.343
Seven.

36:21.245 --> 36:22.712
An adult seven.

36:22.746 --> 36:25.315
[chuckles]

36:25.349 --> 36:29.554
My dad, he's a good man,
but...

36:29.587 --> 36:32.289
he's hard on her.

36:32.323 --> 36:33.791
Cruel sometimes.

36:36.927 --> 36:40.130
He blames her for my mom.

36:40.163 --> 36:42.400
My mom, she died
giving birth, so...

36:44.068 --> 36:45.469
It's not fair.

36:45.502 --> 36:47.605
He knows that,
but he's still...

36:49.740 --> 36:51.642
I don't know.

36:53.477 --> 36:57.949
I try to think of my sister
as a gift my mom left me.

37:03.320 --> 37:05.422
It's stupid, I know.

37:05.456 --> 37:07.157
No, no, no, no, no.

37:07.190 --> 37:09.360
No, no.

37:11.628 --> 37:12.897
Not stupid.

37:18.935 --> 37:21.005
What happened to you...

37:23.206 --> 37:25.243
Maybe it's not a curse.

37:28.045 --> 37:29.580
[door slams]

37:34.819 --> 37:36.454
[speaking Romanian]

37:44.761 --> 37:47.298
-[in English]
Hey, take it easy.
-You, be quiet.

37:48.966 --> 37:50.468
[speaking Romanian]

37:50.968 --> 37:52.937
[stammers]

37:54.672 --> 37:56.641
Shh.

38:04.081 --> 38:05.583
[sniffs]

38:06.850 --> 38:09.786
[dogs barking distantly]

38:09.820 --> 38:12.723
[tense music]

38:18.396 --> 38:20.898
[both panting]

38:36.547 --> 38:37.915
[sighs]

39:17.287 --> 39:18.923
[cigarette case snaps shut]

39:41.245 --> 39:44.382
[gentle music]

40:03.333 --> 40:04.635
[murmurs]

40:11.175 --> 40:12.742
[distant emergency sirens]

40:12.776 --> 40:14.712
[in English]
He shouldn't be this late.

40:18.348 --> 40:20.117
Something's wrong.

40:35.065 --> 40:38.002
[tense music]

40:58.255 --> 40:59.790
It's all gone.

41:04.061 --> 41:06.964
[speaking Romanian]

41:20.244 --> 41:21.212
-[heavy thud]
-[groans]

41:28.151 --> 41:29.787
[grunts]

42:03.821 --> 42:05.890
[groaning]

42:16.099 --> 42:17.701
[spits]

42:38.588 --> 42:40.591
[engine turns off]

42:40.624 --> 42:42.926
-[in English] What's going on?
-Shh, shh.

42:42.959 --> 42:47.230
-[whispering]
-[angry chatter outside]

42:47.264 --> 42:48.666
-[gunshot]
-[man groans]

42:49.432 --> 42:51.835
[man speaking Romanian]

42:52.303 --> 42:55.205
[dramatic music]

43:14.825 --> 43:16.293
[Wesley in English]
You'll be okay.

43:17.994 --> 43:19.797
[woman muttering in Romanian]

43:20.731 --> 43:22.766
[speaking Romanian]

43:29.939 --> 43:31.742
[soldier shouting in Romanian]

43:33.443 --> 43:35.379
[gunshot]

43:41.352 --> 43:43.287
[guns cocking]

43:47.991 --> 43:50.093
[in English]
Tell my sister I love her.

43:50.127 --> 43:52.730
[intense music]

43:54.598 --> 43:57.568
-[all groaning]
-[whooshing]

43:57.601 --> 43:59.670
[both breathing heavily]

44:04.441 --> 44:06.109
Nikolai.

44:06.142 --> 44:08.545
[gasping]

44:08.578 --> 44:09.880
Wesley.

44:09.913 --> 44:11.115
[gunshot]

44:13.050 --> 44:15.986
[tense music]

44:32.669 --> 44:34.738
[speaking Romanian]

44:40.310 --> 44:42.880
[thudding, glass shattering]

44:47.383 --> 44:49.186
[choking]

44:51.655 --> 44:53.023
[grunts]

44:55.659 --> 44:57.795
[rumbling]

45:01.164 --> 45:02.366
[Serghei groaning]

45:10.374 --> 45:12.642
[groans, coughs]

45:12.675 --> 45:15.679
[squelching]

45:15.712 --> 45:18.082
[intense music]

45:27.191 --> 45:31.528
[rumbling fades]

45:31.562 --> 45:34.498
[gentle music]

45:37.334 --> 45:39.269
[clatters]

46:00.323 --> 46:02.526
[birds chirp distantly]

46:04.494 --> 46:06.529
[breathes deeply]

46:06.563 --> 46:09.500
[dramatic music]

46:48.705 --> 46:51.842
[rumbling]

46:56.880 --> 47:00.017
[gentle music]

47:07.523 --> 47:09.426
[muffled shouting]

47:54.204 --> 47:57.140
[sniffling]

48:23.700 --> 48:26.637
[crying]

49:31.301 --> 49:32.636
[knocking]

49:42.412 --> 49:43.747
Nikolai.

49:45.582 --> 49:47.384
Yes.

49:49.419 --> 49:51.288
Thank you for Wesley's letters.

49:52.388 --> 49:55.325
It is an honor
to finally meet you.

49:55.358 --> 49:59.663
Um, he said
you can help me?

50:03.867 --> 50:06.569
I've never tasted
anything so good.

50:06.603 --> 50:08.170
Thank you.

50:08.204 --> 50:11.041
Wesley wrote a lot about you
and your ability.

50:12.976 --> 50:16.713
Elaine, you're interrupting.

50:16.746 --> 50:19.048
I'm sorry, Father.

50:19.081 --> 50:21.685
Dinner only
when you finish practice.

50:26.923 --> 50:29.159
Can you show me
what you can do?

50:31.327 --> 50:32.329
Um...

50:34.430 --> 50:35.998
It doesn't--

50:36.032 --> 50:38.735
It doesn't work like that.

50:38.768 --> 50:42.105
Wesley alluded to the pain
it has brought you.

50:42.138 --> 50:45.241
Perhaps I can help you
control it if we figure out
the variables.

50:45.275 --> 50:48.612
No, no, no, I--
I do not want to control it.

50:48.645 --> 50:50.847
I want to get rid of it.

50:50.881 --> 50:53.583
[tense music]

50:56.786 --> 51:00.724
This-- This thing took...

51:03.760 --> 51:05.395
everyone I love.

51:09.732 --> 51:11.467
I'm sorry, this was a mistake.

51:11.501 --> 51:14.404
Nikolai,
you came here for help.

51:17.006 --> 51:19.409
Is it that you think
you don't deserve it?

51:19.909 --> 51:22.245
Trust me.

51:22.278 --> 51:24.880
I know that feeling well.

51:24.914 --> 51:28.285
Or perhaps it is that you're
afraid to put your trust in me.

51:30.686 --> 51:33.523
We don't know each other,

51:33.557 --> 51:37.327
but you will quickly see
that I do not make promises
I cannot keep.

51:39.062 --> 51:41.564
I'm not sure how much
I'll be able to help.

51:41.597 --> 51:44.267
If there are others like you
we can find,

51:44.300 --> 51:47.236
or if there are experts
that can guide us,

51:47.269 --> 51:49.306
but I'm willing to try.

51:50.840 --> 51:52.375
You're special, Nikolai.

51:54.143 --> 51:57.180
It might be worth
understanding why.

51:57.213 --> 51:59.883
Regardless,

51:59.916 --> 52:02.719
you have a home here
if you want it.

52:02.752 --> 52:05.554
And for what it is worth,

52:05.588 --> 52:08.425
I believe Wesley would
want you to stay.

52:12.662 --> 52:16.399
I'll give you
some time to consider.

52:34.750 --> 52:37.821
[Debussy's "Clair De Lune"
playing on piano]

52:56.239 --> 52:57.440
[music stops]

52:57.474 --> 53:00.810
Don't hover.
Father says it's impolite.

53:09.519 --> 53:12.222
You-- You're friends
with my brother?

53:29.038 --> 53:31.441
I have to get it right first.

53:35.111 --> 53:37.247
Sit.

53:45.288 --> 53:46.723
"Clair De Lune"?

53:46.756 --> 53:48.491
Do you know it?

53:49.859 --> 53:51.995
Yes.

53:52.028 --> 53:53.897
I'm gonna start
from the beginning.

54:56.893 --> 54:59.195
[music fades]

54:59.229 --> 55:02.365
[tense music]

55:07.237 --> 55:10.340
[ventilator hissing]

55:33.563 --> 55:36.399
[Elaine] So you do listen
to my messages.

55:40.136 --> 55:41.404
I've missed you.

55:42.505 --> 55:44.474
I find that hard to believe.

55:47.177 --> 55:48.611
He's getting worse.

55:49.512 --> 55:51.581
Not taking any food.

55:53.716 --> 55:55.585
There isn't much time left.

55:57.720 --> 55:59.989
My presentation
to the investors is in a week.

56:01.524 --> 56:02.925
If I can't show them
a breakthrough,

56:02.959 --> 56:06.095
we'll lose everything
Dad worked for.

56:06.128 --> 56:07.663
Everything we've worked for.

56:07.697 --> 56:09.432
Your last test
killed a man.

56:11.567 --> 56:12.902
-Nikolai--
-If she's not ready,

56:12.936 --> 56:14.304
you'll kill her too.

56:14.337 --> 56:15.538
And embarrass us.

56:15.572 --> 56:17.773
Then make her ready.

56:17.807 --> 56:18.908
Isn't that
what you're doing?

56:23.613 --> 56:25.081
I'll give you more Factor.

56:25.948 --> 56:27.750
Whatever you need.

56:27.784 --> 56:31.854
We're in this together,
brother.

56:31.888 --> 56:34.858
[gentle music]

56:39.795 --> 56:42.866
[sighs]

56:45.702 --> 56:46.703
Thank you.

56:48.104 --> 56:49.038
Give us a moment.

56:50.740 --> 56:51.941
Of course.

56:53.642 --> 56:55.745
He always liked you best.

57:12.829 --> 57:15.765
[gentle music]
